ws/abstract-cpp-component-extensions.md). A class marked as `abstract` can be a base class, but it cannot be instantiated.  \n  \n## Example  \nThe following sample generates C3622.  \n  \n```  \n// C3622.cpp  \n// compile with: /clr  \nref class a abstract {};  \n  \nint main() {  \n   a aa;   // C3622  \n}  \n```  \n"}